			<h1>COMC-115</h1>
			<h2>A+ Core Hardware Concepts</h2>	
			<p>
				This is a hardware prep class where you learn the basic parts of a computer and how to put them together. The goal of the class is for students to come away with the knowledge that they need in order to debug a computer 
			</p>
			
			<p>
				This semester students built a bare-bones computer from the ground up, every one who leaves the class can say that they built a computer.
			</p>
			
			<h3 class="listHead">topics include</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>RAM</li>
				<li>SSD and HDD</li>
				<li>basic audio</li>
				<li>power supplies</li>
				<li>cmos</li>
				<li>bios</li>
				<li>display screens</li>
				<li>cpus</li>
				<li>motherboards</li>
				<li>troubleshooting</li>
				<li>port connectors</li>
				<li>expasion card intsallation</li>
				<li><em>and much more</em></li>
			</ul>
		
